1
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:40,467
<i>Dear, I really believe
your sister Coleen</i>

2
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:42,467
<i>- didn't kill you.
- You're a bastard, Manuel!</i>

3
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:44,233
<i>What the hell
are you talking about?</i>

4
00:00:44,367 --> 00:00:45,533
<i> Can you stop already?</i>

5
00:00:45,667 --> 00:00:46,733
<i>If you don't, I swear
I'm going take you on!</i>

6
00:00:49,733 --> 00:00:50,533
<i> Hello, Mom?</i>

7
00:00:50,667 --> 00:00:51,833
<i> Stop disrespecting our child</i>

8
00:00:51,967 --> 00:00:53,900
<i>and ruining what's left
of her memory!</i>

9
00:00:54,033 --> 00:00:56,300
<i>- Was that Hazel?
- Dad asked me to go with him</i>

10
00:00:56,433 --> 00:00:57,567
<i> so he could talk to Hazel.</i>

11
00:00:57,700 --> 00:00:59,300
<i> Bring your father home!</i>

12
00:00:59,433 --> 00:01:00,833
<i> Why did you meet with Hazel</i>

13
00:01:00,967 --> 00:01:02,500
<i> without telling me?</i>

14
00:01:02,633 --> 00:01:04,733
<i>So you're scared to be far
from me?</i>

15
00:01:04,867 --> 00:01:08,167
<i>I'm just scared of what Hazel
might do to you.</i>

16
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:10,867
<i>Hazel can't take me away
from you anymore.</i>

17
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:11,967
<i> Jessica...</i>

18
00:01:12,100 --> 00:01:13,033
<i>- Jessica...
- Dear!</i>

19
00:01:14,433 --> 00:01:16,700
<i>- Sweetie! Sweetie!
- Jessica!</i>

20
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:19,767
<i>Guilt is a natural part
of grief.</i>

21
00:01:19,900 --> 00:01:24,433
<i>What you're describing sounds
like survivor's guilt.</i>

22
00:01:24,567 --> 00:01:26,733
<i> I failed her, Doc.</i>

23
00:01:26,867 --> 00:01:29,700
<i> I failed Jessica.</i>

24
00:01:29,833 --> 00:01:31,867
<i>Felma, what did the doctor say?</i>

25
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,867
<i>Coleen's guilt runs really deep.</i>

26
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:38,733
<i>We need to keep
reminding her that...</i>

27
00:01:38,867 --> 00:01:41,333
<i> none of this was her fault.</i>

28
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:44,533
<i> Coleen's situation is so hard.</i>

29
00:01:44,667 --> 00:01:47,967
<i>Manuel, on the other hand,
is quiet.</i>

30
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:51,400
<i>You can see how broken he is
after Jessica died.</i>

31
00:01:51,533 --> 00:01:53,467
<i>Come on, try to smile a little.</i>

32
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:56,167
<i>Someone left a gift for you
at the guard house.</i>

33
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:58,200
<i>- Rolly said so.
- A gift?</i>

34
00:01:58,333 --> 00:01:59,533
<i> Here.</i>

35
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:03,800
<i>- Hazel did that!
- Who else?</i>

36
00:02:06,267 --> 00:02:08,500
<i>- What?
- You demon!</i>

37
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:10,867
<i> What did you send me?</i>

38
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,167
You got it already?

39
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:13,867
That was fast.

40
00:02:14,567 --> 00:02:18,133
Just a little reminder that
my daughter's blood

41
00:02:18,267 --> 00:02:19,900
is on your hands.

42
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:21,267
Especially Coleen's.

43
00:02:22,233 --> 00:02:23,500
Because she killed Jessica.

44
00:02:24,833 --> 00:02:26,000
You know what, Hazel?

45
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:30,767
If you have evidence to support
your crazy claims...

46
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:34,000
go ahead and file a case.

47
00:02:34,133 --> 00:02:36,167
Coleen and I will face you!

48
00:02:36,767 --> 00:02:38,967
Maybe then you'll stop
demonizing my daughter!

49
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,367
Are you challenging me?

50
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:42,500
<i> Yes!</i>

51
00:02:43,767 --> 00:02:45,300
Chill, Felma.

52
00:02:45,433 --> 00:02:46,833
We'll get there.

53
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:47,867
<i> Really?</i>

54
00:02:48,633 --> 00:02:49,933
What's taking so long?

55
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:52,967
If you have evidence,
go and sue us.

56
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:55,867
You want trouble, Hazel?

57
00:02:56,567 --> 00:02:59,400
Fine, I'll give you trouble.

58
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,867
Get ready for what I'm about
to do!

59
00:03:03,500 --> 00:03:04,467
Go on then.

60
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:05,567
What are you planning?

61
00:03:05,700 --> 00:03:07,100
Give me a clue.

62
00:03:08,733 --> 00:03:09,600
It's Manuel.

63
00:03:11,033 --> 00:03:14,367
I'm going to use Manuel
against you.

64
00:03:30,033 --> 00:03:33,533
Wow, girl! So fierce!

65
00:03:33,667 --> 00:03:36,100
First time I've heard my bestie

66
00:03:36,233 --> 00:03:38,567
spit out bad words like that!

67
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:40,833
War freak mode on!

68
00:03:40,967 --> 00:03:42,300
There!

69
00:03:42,433 --> 00:03:43,800
Well, it's true!

70
00:03:44,267 --> 00:03:46,533
You know, Hazel's been messing
with me for a long time!

71
00:03:46,667 --> 00:03:47,633
So what's your plan?

72
00:03:47,767 --> 00:03:49,833
Wait, why is Manuel involved?

73
00:03:51,333 --> 00:03:54,200
I'm going to give Hazel
the nightmare she deserves.

74
00:03:56,567 --> 00:03:58,033
I'm going to talk to Manuel.

75
00:03:59,133 --> 00:04:01,067
I'm going to push him
to speed up the annulment.

76
00:04:02,533 --> 00:04:05,367
I'm taking her out
of Manuel's life.

77
00:04:06,700 --> 00:04:08,467
There it is!

78
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:12,100
My Felma's inner warrior
has arrived!

79
00:04:12,233 --> 00:04:15,600
Oh, I like it, girl!
You go, girl!

80
00:04:15,733 --> 00:04:16,900
Stop it.

81
00:04:31,233 --> 00:04:32,233
Manuel?

82
00:04:33,167 --> 00:04:34,500
Felma, come in.

83
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:40,467
I wanted to tell you something.

84
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:43,833
Me, too, I also wanted
to tell you something.

85
00:04:44,533 --> 00:04:45,867
But go ahead, you first.

86
00:04:46,367 --> 00:04:48,833
No, you go.

87
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,767
It's...

88
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:56,933
about the annulment with Hazel.

89
00:04:57,433 --> 00:05:00,000
Didn't I promise you that once
I got out of the hospital,

90
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:03,100
I'd take care of it right away?

91
00:05:03,267 --> 00:05:06,400
It's just that so much
has happened.

92
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:11,267
Felma, it's not that I don't
want to do it, I do.

93
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:12,400
I really do.

94
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:13,933
But...

95
00:05:15,167 --> 00:05:19,100
I just have so much on my mind.

96
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:25,400
I feel like I need
to breathe first,

97
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:27,100
pick myself up again.

98
00:05:28,133 --> 00:05:29,533
Maybe I need to...

99
00:05:30,633 --> 00:05:32,733
accept that Jessica is gone.

100
00:05:33,533 --> 00:05:35,533
And second, I need to make sure

101
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:37,633
Coleen doesn't end up in jail.

102
00:05:40,733 --> 00:05:41,633
Oh...

103
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:43,567
I understand.

104
00:05:45,267 --> 00:05:46,567
I can wait.

105
00:05:47,733 --> 00:05:49,267
Thank you, Felma.

106
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,933
So what were you going to say?

107
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,500
Actually, the same thing.

108
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:04,500
I just wanted to ask...

109
00:06:05,733 --> 00:06:07,633
if we can focus on Coleen first.

110
00:06:08,333 --> 00:06:09,767
Oh, right.

111
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:12,667
- Coleen first.
- Okay.

112
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:28,233
What are you doing, friend?

113
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,500
Looking for someone willing
to testify

114
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,833
that Coleen pushed Jessica.

115
00:06:36,867 --> 00:06:38,033
Are you serious?

116
00:06:39,267 --> 00:06:41,400
Serious and desperate, Alice.

117
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:46,900
I promised Jessica,
I'd put Coleen in jail.

118
00:06:48,667 --> 00:06:50,533
The driver who hit her

119
00:06:50,667 --> 00:06:52,267
is the one who should be
jailed, Hazel.

120
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:55,367
And you're seriously using
nurses to fabricate evidence?

121
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:57,567
You think anyone
will agree to that?

122
00:06:57,700 --> 00:07:00,067
What, are you going to stop me?

123
00:07:01,433 --> 00:07:04,767
Who knows?
Someone might say yes.

124
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:06,600
Someone might need the money.

125
00:07:06,733 --> 00:07:09,800
Would they refuse if I give them

126
00:07:09,933 --> 00:07:13,467
the money meant for our tickets
back to Canada?

127
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:17,633
That's more than a hundred
thousand pesos.

128
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,400
I'm sorry, friend.

129
00:07:19,533 --> 00:07:20,867
But if you want to hire

130
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,767
someone like Maximo, go ahead.

131
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:27,033
But fellow nurses? No,
I'm not letting that happen.

132
00:07:27,167 --> 00:07:29,000
<i> Mrs. Cruz!</i>

133
00:07:29,133 --> 00:07:31,333
<i>- Mrs. Cruz?
- Attorney Salazar..</i>

134
00:07:31,467 --> 00:07:33,867
Just a minute.

135
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,233
<i> Mrs. Cruz!</i>

136
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,667
<i> Mrs. Cruz!</i>

137
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,100
I've been calling you.

138
00:07:40,233 --> 00:07:41,233
Why aren't you answering?

139
00:07:41,367 --> 00:07:42,600
Why, Attorney?

140
00:07:42,733 --> 00:07:44,133
Is it good news?

141
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,400
Very good news.

142
00:07:47,567 --> 00:07:51,700
The driver who hit Jessica
is already in police custody.

143
00:07:51,833 --> 00:07:53,433
He turned himself in.

144
00:07:53,567 --> 00:07:54,667
<i> Really, Attorney?</i>

145
00:07:55,967 --> 00:07:59,800
Friend, you don't seem happy
about Attorney's news.

146
00:08:00,967 --> 00:08:01,967
I'm happy.

147
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:05,467
Very happy.

148
00:08:14,133 --> 00:08:15,900
Boss, I'd like to speak

149
00:08:16,033 --> 00:08:16,967
with the suspect
who turned himself in

150
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:19,600
for Jessica Cruz's
hit-and-run case.

151
00:08:19,733 --> 00:08:20,933
Where is he?

152
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,700
Where's the man
who killed my daughter?

153
00:08:22,833 --> 00:08:24,367
Where is he?

154
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:27,467
- Where is he?
- Mrs. Cruz, please calm down!

155
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:29,000
Mrs. Cruz!

156
00:08:30,667 --> 00:08:32,167
<i> You monster.</i>

157
00:08:32,967 --> 00:08:35,700
- Animal! Animal!
- Ma'am! Ma'am!

158
00:08:35,833 --> 00:08:37,900
- I'm sorry! Ma'am! I'm sorry!
- That's enough!

159
00:08:38,033 --> 00:08:39,867
- That's enough!
- I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

160
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:43,000
- I didn't mean it!
- I'll never accept your sorry!

161
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:45,767
- I didn't mean it!
- You killed my daughter!

162
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,700
I got scared, that's why I ran.

163
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:49,267
But I regret it.

164
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:51,200
I saw you on FriendsBook.

165
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:53,033
So I turned myself in.

166
00:08:53,167 --> 00:08:55,367
Regret?
My daughter is dead!

167
00:08:55,533 --> 00:08:57,567
- She's gone! Let go of me!
- Mrs. Cruz.

168
00:08:57,700 --> 00:08:59,400
- Let go of me!
- Mrs. Cruz.

169
00:08:59,533 --> 00:09:01,400
- I'm sorry.
- You animal!

170
00:09:01,533 --> 00:09:02,633
I'm really sorry!

171
00:09:02,767 --> 00:09:03,700
What's going on here?

172
00:09:03,833 --> 00:09:05,533
- Sarge!
- You animal! Let go...

173
00:09:05,667 --> 00:09:06,833
Wait!

174
00:09:06,967 --> 00:09:09,267
- Sarge.
- Kill! Just kill him!

175
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:10,067
We're sorry.

176
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,367
My apologies.

177
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:13,567
Mrs. Cruz is my client.

178
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:15,533
She's Jessica Cruz's mother.

179
00:09:15,667 --> 00:09:18,267
Sorry, she couldn't
control her emotions.

180
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:20,167
You know the rules, Attorney.

181
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:24,333
We don't allow violence here,
even toward a suspect.

182
00:09:24,467 --> 00:09:25,700
Sarge, we're really sorry.

183
00:09:25,833 --> 00:09:28,567
Sir, I don't care.
Kill him, too!

184
00:09:28,733 --> 00:09:30,767
- This won't happen again.
- It will never...

185
00:09:30,900 --> 00:09:33,067
My daughter is gone forever.
Kill him!

186
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:35,267
Mrs. Cruz, let's go!

187
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,600
No, wait!

188
00:09:36,733 --> 00:09:38,667
- Mrs. Cruz!
- Let go of me! No!

189
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,633
Wait! You animal!

190
00:09:40,767 --> 00:09:43,100
<i>- You animal!
- I'm really sorry!</i>

191
00:09:44,933 --> 00:09:46,800
Let go of me, Attorney!

192
00:09:46,933 --> 00:09:47,867
Let go of me!

193
00:09:49,533 --> 00:09:51,167
You animal!

194
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,267
Earlier today, he surrendered
himself to authorities.

195
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:55,500
Timothy Malabanan,

196
00:09:55,633 --> 00:09:57,733
better known as Timo,

197
00:09:57,867 --> 00:10:00,633
the driver involved
in the hit-and-run

198
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,733
that killed Jessica
Capistrano Cruz,

199
00:10:03,867 --> 00:10:05,767
<i> 18 years old.</i>

200
00:10:05,900 --> 00:10:07,933
<i>Malabanan refused
to give a statement,</i>

201
00:10:08,067 --> 00:10:10,100
<i>but we were able
to capture video</i>

202
00:10:10,233 --> 00:10:11,800
<i> of Mrs. Hazel Cruz,</i>

203
00:10:11,933 --> 00:10:14,767
<i>the victim's mother, arriving,
leading to a heated</i>

204
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:17,200
<i> confrontation between them.</i>

205
00:10:17,333 --> 00:10:18,767
<i> You animal! You animal!</i>

206
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:20,400
Hazel charged at him right away?

207
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:23,100
<i>- Let go of me!
- I'm sorry!</i>

208
00:10:23,233 --> 00:10:24,467
<i> Sorry?</i>

209
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:25,867
<i>I will never accept your sorry!</i>

210
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,333
<i> I didn't mean it.</i>

211
00:10:27,467 --> 00:10:30,667
To be fair, this is the first
time that it didn't piss me off,

212
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:32,400
that Hazel's monstrous behavior.

213
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:33,500
<i> I just watched you in...</i>

214
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,000
- Same.
- Friendsbook. So...

215
00:10:35,167 --> 00:10:36,033
<i> I turned myself in.</i>

216
00:10:36,167 --> 00:10:38,700
Maybe now she'll finally
leave Coleen alone.

217
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:40,000
There, that's
the actual suspect.

218
00:10:40,133 --> 00:10:41,267
<i> Let go of me!</i>

219
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:42,033
<i>- Mrs. Cruz....
- Let go of me!</i>

220
00:10:42,167 --> 00:10:42,933
Manuel?

221
00:10:43,067 --> 00:10:45,400
<i>- I'm sorry.
- You animal!</i>

222
00:10:45,533 --> 00:10:49,200
Attorney, I want to speak
to Timo Malabanan.

223
00:10:50,233 --> 00:10:51,133
Okay.

224
00:10:51,267 --> 00:10:53,600
Okay, I'll secure a permit.

225
00:10:56,167 --> 00:10:57,433
Not now.

226
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:00,233
Do it when you've calmed down.

227
00:11:02,033 --> 00:11:05,100
<i>We also tried to get
Mrs. Hazel Cruz's statement,</i>

228
00:11:05,233 --> 00:11:06,900
<i> but she refused.</i>

229
00:11:07,033 --> 00:11:09,667
<i> For PNTV 42 Newsline Flash,</i>

230
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:12,333
<i> this is Jiro Gomez.</i>

231
00:11:12,467 --> 00:11:17,533
<i>Committed, Truthful, Sincere,
Whole-hearted.</i>

232
00:11:21,367 --> 00:11:23,100
So what happens now, Attorney?

233
00:11:24,233 --> 00:11:27,367
Well, the prosecutor will file
a case against the suspect.

234
00:11:28,367 --> 00:11:30,567
So the focus is now
on Timo Malabanan?

235
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:33,300
Coleen's out of the picture?

236
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:34,633
We still have to wait

237
00:11:34,767 --> 00:11:38,133
for the suspect's
official sworn statement.

238
00:11:38,267 --> 00:11:39,500
But I didn't see Coleen

239
00:11:39,633 --> 00:11:41,700
under the list of suspects
in the investigation report,

240
00:11:41,867 --> 00:11:46,233
so I guess Malabanan
is really the focus now.

241
00:11:46,367 --> 00:11:48,233
Hazel's the only one accusing
Coleen anyway.

242
00:11:49,067 --> 00:11:50,533
And now that the suspect
has been identified.

243
00:11:50,667 --> 00:11:52,100
She should stop already.

244
00:11:52,233 --> 00:11:53,100
She really should.

245
00:11:54,467 --> 00:11:55,833
She's been zeroing in on Coleen

246
00:11:55,967 --> 00:11:58,700
just because she couldn't find
anyone else to blame.

247
00:11:59,733 --> 00:12:00,967
But now that the one
who killed Jessica

248
00:12:01,100 --> 00:12:04,667
will face the consequences,
she should finally quiet down.

249
00:12:05,533 --> 00:12:07,133
Thank God.

250
00:12:08,367 --> 00:12:11,067
Coleen can finally sleep
peacefully again.

251
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:13,233
Her nightmare is about to end.

252
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:16,200
Our nightmare.

253
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:27,233
Lord, thank you.

254
00:12:27,367 --> 00:12:30,300
My goddaughter
will finally get justice.

255
00:12:31,567 --> 00:12:32,700
No, Alice.

256
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:37,200
Even if this Timo
ends up in jail,

257
00:12:37,333 --> 00:12:40,400
Jessica will still not get
the full justice she deserves.

258
00:12:41,467 --> 00:12:43,333
Are you still talking
about Coleen, Hazel?

259
00:12:43,467 --> 00:12:44,633
Yes.

260
00:12:44,767 --> 00:12:46,333
It shouldn't
only be Timo who pays

261
00:12:46,467 --> 00:12:47,667
for what happened to Jessica.

262
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:50,533
Hazel, stop going after the kid.

263
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:54,333
Kid? She acts like a kid!

264
00:12:54,467 --> 00:12:56,033
But she's not a kid anymore.

265
00:12:56,167 --> 00:12:57,467
You forgot?

266
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:59,867
She's even older than Jessica.

267
00:13:00,967 --> 00:13:02,800
I won't stop

268
00:13:02,933 --> 00:13:05,300
until that "sisig girl"
is behind bars.

269
00:13:07,433 --> 00:13:08,533
<i> Mrs. Cruz!</i>

270
00:13:10,067 --> 00:13:12,000
<i>- Alice!
- Wait, I'll get it.</i>

271
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:13,633
<i> Mrs. Cruz!</i>

272
00:13:15,733 --> 00:13:17,100
<i> Attorney.</i>

273
00:13:17,233 --> 00:13:20,567
Friend, Attorney Salazar
brought pizza.

274
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,600
It's time for celebration.

275
00:13:23,733 --> 00:13:24,633
Attorney...

276
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:28,167
I want to see Timo again.

277
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:30,233
Mrs. Cruz.

278
00:13:31,467 --> 00:13:34,300
Sergeant Delfin
already warned us.

279
00:13:34,433 --> 00:13:35,833
I just want to talk to him.

280
00:13:35,967 --> 00:13:37,100
I'm not going to hurt him.

281
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:39,067
But, Mrs. Cruz...

282
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:40,433
Attorney.

283
00:13:42,167 --> 00:13:43,567
I just want closure.

284
00:13:45,167 --> 00:13:46,200
Just closure.

285
00:13:47,567 --> 00:13:48,933
Please?

286
00:13:49,067 --> 00:13:51,500
Okay, fine.

287
00:13:52,867 --> 00:13:56,633
I'll request
a new visitation permit.

288
00:13:57,233 --> 00:13:58,367
Thank you.

289
00:14:35,567 --> 00:14:37,267
This is Jessica.

290
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:41,433
My only child.

291
00:14:42,933 --> 00:14:44,867
I loved her so much.

292
00:14:45,767 --> 00:14:47,733
She was my life.

293
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:50,533
Why did you run her over?

294
00:14:50,933 --> 00:14:52,467
Ma'am, I'm sorry.

295
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:54,400
I really didn't mean it.

296
00:14:54,533 --> 00:14:57,367
She suddenly crossed the street.

297
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:59,133
I wasn't able to hit the brakes.

298
00:14:59,267 --> 00:15:01,100
Why didn't you avoid her?

299
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:04,367
It all happened so fast.

300
00:15:05,767 --> 00:15:08,300
And I was driving fast, too.

301
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:10,500
I'm sorry.

302
00:15:10,633 --> 00:15:12,500
I swear I didn't mean it.

303
00:15:14,467 --> 00:15:16,800
Let me reverse the situation.

304
00:15:19,767 --> 00:15:21,500
Jessica is your child.

305
00:15:22,533 --> 00:15:24,467
I run her over.

306
00:15:26,333 --> 00:15:27,367
Then...

307
00:15:29,867 --> 00:15:31,367
I flee.

308
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:36,633
Do you think you'd forgive me?

309
00:15:37,667 --> 00:15:40,433
I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

310
00:15:40,567 --> 00:15:42,000
It's like you killed me, too.

311
00:15:43,433 --> 00:15:46,233
It feels like you're killing me
over and over.

312
00:15:47,733 --> 00:15:51,100
What you did to my daughter
hurt so much.

313
00:15:52,333 --> 00:15:54,700
And what you're doing to me
hurts even more.

314
00:15:56,733 --> 00:15:59,500
- She's gone...
- I'm so sorry.

315
00:15:59,633 --> 00:16:02,000
My daughter is gone,
she's dead.

316
00:16:05,433 --> 00:16:06,433
Ouch.

317
00:16:09,133 --> 00:16:11,000
Mrs. Cruz...

318
00:16:11,133 --> 00:16:13,200
My stomach just hurt.

319
00:16:14,233 --> 00:16:17,167
I'll be back, okay?
Just a moment.

320
00:16:18,867 --> 00:16:19,933
Boss.

321
00:16:20,067 --> 00:16:21,333
Watch them, okay?

322
00:16:21,467 --> 00:16:23,633
You handle things here for now.

323
00:16:23,767 --> 00:16:24,833
All right.

324
00:16:24,967 --> 00:16:26,300
If my client tries
anything stupid

325
00:16:26,433 --> 00:16:28,300
with the suspect,
restrain her, okay?

326
00:16:28,433 --> 00:16:30,167
- I got it.
- I'll be back.

327
00:16:40,733 --> 00:16:41,733
This.

328
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:45,567
Is this your family?

329
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:49,467
Ma'am...

330
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:52,033
Why do you have a picture
of my wife and child?

331
00:17:00,533 --> 00:17:02,233
I miss you so much, dear.

332
00:17:05,167 --> 00:17:07,267
I miss you so much.

333
00:17:07,633 --> 00:17:08,533
Come on, sweetie.

334
00:17:09,033 --> 00:17:11,000
You need to get near
your sister.

335
00:17:11,133 --> 00:17:14,167
You're the one to tell her
the good news.

336
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,300
Jessica.

337
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:27,667
The one who hit you
has surrendered.

338
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,433
Justice will finally
be served for your death.

339
00:17:33,533 --> 00:17:35,067
You can finally rest.

340
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:37,200
Sorry.

341
00:17:40,333 --> 00:17:43,333
I'm sorry again
that I couldn't save you.

342
00:17:45,133 --> 00:17:46,433
Coleen.

343
00:17:46,567 --> 00:17:50,100
Dear, I know your sister.

344
00:17:50,267 --> 00:17:52,067
I know her very well.

345
00:17:53,633 --> 00:17:56,933
And I know in my heart,
she doesn't blame you.

346
00:17:58,067 --> 00:17:59,433
Especially now...

347
00:18:01,867 --> 00:18:03,800
that justice
has been served.

348
00:18:08,267 --> 00:18:09,767
I'm sorry, Dad...

349
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:23,667
Where did you get that?

350
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:26,300
Why do you have a picture
of my family?

351
00:18:32,300 --> 00:18:34,167
Where did you get that?

352
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:36,733
Why do you have a picture
of my family?

353
00:18:52,167 --> 00:18:54,233
<i> Lord, thank you.</i>

354
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:57,600
<i>Finally, justice will be served
for my godchild's death.</i>

355
00:18:58,933 --> 00:19:00,767
Is this your family?

356
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:03,067
Ma'am, please, I'm begging you.

357
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,667
Don't hurt my family.

358
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:09,767
Hurt them?

359
00:19:11,767 --> 00:19:13,200
I won't hurt them.

360
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:16,167
I'll help them.

361
00:19:18,133 --> 00:19:18,967
What?

362
00:19:24,567 --> 00:19:26,133
I went to your house.

363
00:19:27,233 --> 00:19:29,333
I spoke to your wife.

364
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:31,000
Turns out she's unemployed...

365
00:19:32,367 --> 00:19:33,733
and pregnant.

366
00:19:35,967 --> 00:19:38,300
She only sells barbecue.

367
00:19:42,767 --> 00:19:45,933
That 20,000 pesos you left...

368
00:19:47,967 --> 00:19:48,867
do you think...

369
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:51,900
that would be enough?

370
00:19:57,067 --> 00:19:59,167
I feel sorry for your children.

371
00:19:59,300 --> 00:20:01,167
Poor kids.

372
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:02,133
Ma'am.

373
00:20:03,867 --> 00:20:05,200
Don't worry.

374
00:20:06,233 --> 00:20:12,133
I'll give Diana 100,000 pesos...

375
00:20:15,633 --> 00:20:17,900
so she can start
even a small business.

376
00:20:19,167 --> 00:20:20,500
Isn't that good?

377
00:20:24,733 --> 00:20:28,833
You wouldn't do this without
expecting something in return.

378
00:20:32,267 --> 00:20:33,533
What is that?

379
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:36,867
You're easy to talk to.

380
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:39,467
Looks like we understand
each other.

381
00:20:42,267 --> 00:20:43,267
Don't worry,

382
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:46,167
I'll make it easy for you.

383
00:21:06,433 --> 00:21:08,233
Hey, Andrea,
Jessica is upset.

384
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,733
She said you didn't visit her.

385
00:21:09,867 --> 00:21:11,033
No, that's not true!

386
00:21:11,167 --> 00:21:13,033
Joel and I went,
but when we arrived,

387
00:21:13,167 --> 00:21:14,533
you were already gone.

388
00:21:14,667 --> 00:21:15,467
Sorry, sorry.

389
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:17,333
- That's true.
- We couldn't keep up

390
00:21:17,467 --> 00:21:18,533
with you guys.

391
00:21:18,667 --> 00:21:20,367
My fault, I asked Andrea
to go with me to the doctor.

392
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:22,133
- Sorry.
- Oh, Joel.

393
00:21:22,267 --> 00:21:24,533
Don't take them seriously.

394
00:21:24,667 --> 00:21:26,200
That's just how
they show affection.

395
00:21:27,367 --> 00:21:28,233
That's right.

396
00:21:28,367 --> 00:21:29,567
There's no affection
on his face, though.

397
00:21:33,867 --> 00:21:35,867
- Auntie Felma.
- Oh?

398
00:21:36,433 --> 00:21:37,200
Uncle Manuel.

399
00:21:37,800 --> 00:21:41,433
Andrea and I talked.

400
00:21:43,967 --> 00:21:45,133
What did you talk about?

401
00:21:46,433 --> 00:21:47,733
I think they talked about
marriage

402
00:21:47,867 --> 00:21:49,600
Hey, Jeff, no way!

403
00:21:49,733 --> 00:21:51,400
- Jeff!
- Marriage!

404
00:21:51,533 --> 00:21:52,733
I'm losing it.

405
00:21:52,867 --> 00:21:55,400
- Mom, can I...
- Oh, what is it...

406
00:21:55,533 --> 00:21:58,900
We talked about
possibly going...

407
00:21:59,900 --> 00:22:03,033
on a vacation in Laguna
with Coleen,

408
00:22:03,167 --> 00:22:04,967
so she can relax.

409
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:06,633
Just you two?

410
00:22:06,767 --> 00:22:08,600
- That's great!
- No, all of us.

411
00:22:08,733 --> 00:22:10,367
- Family vacation.
- I see.

412
00:22:10,500 --> 00:22:11,567
Oh, that's mine.

413
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:13,567
Maybe it's my Sakay delivery.

414
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:14,500
I ordered dessert.

415
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:16,333
- Okay.
- There, stay outside.

416
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:18,333
You know, Joel,
I like that plan.

417
00:22:18,467 --> 00:22:19,600
Yes, it's a good idea.

418
00:22:19,733 --> 00:22:21,767
At least we can try to forget
our problems for a while.

419
00:22:21,900 --> 00:22:23,600
Well, let's plan it
properly, Mom.

420
00:22:23,733 --> 00:22:24,600
Do you want this weekend?

421
00:22:24,733 --> 00:22:25,733
- Mom?
- Yes, sure.

422
00:22:25,867 --> 00:22:28,433
Just include your Auntie Paz
and Uncle Abel.

423
00:22:28,567 --> 00:22:30,333
- Where's your delivery?
- Hi, good evening.

424
00:22:30,467 --> 00:22:33,900
Sorry if I interrupted
your family dinner.

425
00:22:34,033 --> 00:22:36,067
Attorney, is there a problem?

426
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:37,300
Yes.

427
00:22:39,033 --> 00:22:46,400
Well, Malabanan released
a new statement.

428
00:22:47,133 --> 00:22:48,100
He added some details,

429
00:22:48,233 --> 00:22:53,267
and he said he remembered
someone pushing Jessica

430
00:22:54,067 --> 00:22:55,067
before he hit her.

431
00:22:56,167 --> 00:22:59,367
And the description
in the police sketch...

432
00:22:59,500 --> 00:23:01,167
it matched Coleen.

433
00:23:07,333 --> 00:23:08,233
<i> No...</i>

434
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:10,933
No...

435
00:23:13,933 --> 00:23:14,933
Attorney.

436
00:23:15,533 --> 00:23:16,633
Mrs. Cruz.

437
00:23:17,833 --> 00:23:19,533
Tell me the truth.

438
00:23:21,633 --> 00:23:24,867
What did you say to Timo
while I was gone?

439
00:23:25,633 --> 00:23:26,667
Excuse me?

440
00:23:27,333 --> 00:23:31,300
He added details to his
statement after you two talked.

441
00:23:32,067 --> 00:23:33,267
About the pushing.

442
00:23:34,367 --> 00:23:35,367
So?

443
00:23:36,267 --> 00:23:37,333
What are you implying?

444
00:23:37,467 --> 00:23:38,667
That I told him to do it?

445
00:23:39,167 --> 00:23:40,433
Mrs. Cruz, I'm not implying.

446
00:23:40,567 --> 00:23:41,800
I'm asking.

447
00:23:42,267 --> 00:23:47,200
If it's true that Timo
saw Coleen push Jessica,

448
00:23:47,700 --> 00:23:50,367
he should have said
so in his first statement.

449
00:23:51,300 --> 00:23:52,600
Why only now?

450
00:23:53,233 --> 00:23:55,533
After you two were alone?

451
00:23:56,500 --> 00:23:58,000
Come on, Attorney.

452
00:23:58,133 --> 00:23:59,900
Instead of all the accusations
you're throwing,

453
00:24:00,033 --> 00:24:01,467
just get ready.

454
00:24:02,167 --> 00:24:04,800
Get ready for the case
we're filing against Coleen.

455
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:06,500
Here it is.

456
00:24:06,633 --> 00:24:08,433
The one we've all been
waiting for.

457
00:24:08,567 --> 00:24:09,567
It's here.

458
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:16,467
Who are you?

459
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:18,100
I'm Coleen's mother.

460
00:24:18,933 --> 00:24:19,933
Who's Coleen?

461
00:24:20,067 --> 00:24:23,033
The one you said
pushed Jessica Cruz.

462
00:24:23,167 --> 00:24:24,533
I don't want to talk to you.

463
00:24:24,667 --> 00:24:26,067
Sir, take me back to my cell.

464
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:27,567
Put me back!

465
00:24:27,700 --> 00:24:29,400
Sir! Put me back there!

466
00:24:29,567 --> 00:24:31,200
How much did Hazel give you?

467
00:24:33,733 --> 00:24:35,633
We have word
from the Fiscal's Office.

468
00:24:35,767 --> 00:24:39,033
Hazel has already filed a case
against Coleen.

469
00:24:39,167 --> 00:24:41,267
Oh no. Coleen might not be able
to handle that.

470
00:24:44,767 --> 00:24:45,800
Coleen?

471
00:24:45,933 --> 00:24:47,833
Time to eat.

472
00:24:47,967 --> 00:24:50,167
Coleen, can you hear me?
